The few time I’ve called in to order for pick up the guys there are just so not wanting to take your order. BEST PIZZA EVER. Seriously, this is my #1 go to spot since it opened a year ago or so and by far the best, real  pizza around. I like to get either  sausage or presetting as my toppings. And if I order plain cheese I like to get extra cheese, its still not a ton of cheese but I feel like it makes the pie a little better since it takes about 10 minutes to get it home for me to devour. I also always ask for the home made hot pepper flakes to go, love them. The sauce is amazing too, and the crust is crunchy yet chewy, perfect! I always call at 4:00 on the dot to make sure I can pick up my pizza when I want and not have to wait the 2 hours or so it takes if you call any later. So happy to have real NY pizza back in my life! Rosella's draws a huge lunch crowd, which makes it busy, and I've been to a lot of NYC pizzerias that are packed and have staff with positive attitudes. I was craving something flavorful for lunch but the  Indian place I wanted to go to was closed. I didn't bring my phone with me because I was picking up a quick lunch so I couldn't find the Thai place which was my second choice.  Big Pizza sign. NYC pizza is always great, what could go wrong?  $5 for the eggplant slice. Ouch. The crust was a bit thick and spongy. Slice was heated but still cold. I was starving, so I ate it. Halfway through the slice I was starting to accept that I didn't like it.  The crust reminded me of sweet Elios. The sauce was sweet. I finished it feeling sad, still hungry, and feeling like an ass for not just going back into the office, getting my phone, and finding the That thai place ($8 lunch special), or at least a place with better reviews.  Maybe tourists eat here?  I'm still hungry.
